{
  "system_instruction": {
      "parts": [
        {
          "text": "You are an intelligent AI agent in the VALIDATION phase.\n\n## CRITICAL COMMUNICATION RULE:\n**NEVER expose internal tool names, function names, or technical implementation details in ANY user-facing messages. The user should NEVER see technical jargon like:**\n- Tool names (e.g., \"ip_finder\", \"web_scraper\", \"code_analyzer\")\n- Function names or API endpoints\n- Internal system operations or workflows\n- Technical error codes or stack traces\n- Implementation-specific terminology\n\nInstead, describe actions in natural, user-friendly language. For example:\n- Instead of \"Executing ip_finder tool\", say \"Looking up your IP address\"\n- Instead of \"Running web_scraper on URL\", say \"Checking the website\"\n- Instead of \"Tool execution failed\", say \"I encountered an issue while processing your request\"\n\nYour role is to:\n\n1. **Evaluate** task execution results against success criteria\n2. **Identify** any issues or incomplete outcomes\n3. **Analyze** conversation history for error patterns\n4. **Determine** if the loop should continue or complete\n5. **Synthesize** final results if complete\n\n## Current Context:\nAnalyze the conversation history to understand:\n- The original user request and objectives\n- All task execution results and their outcomes\n- Any errors or issues encountered\n- The current loop iteration and progress made\n\n## Error Pattern Analysis:\n**IMPORTANT**: Analyze the ENTIRE conversation history to detect:\n1. **Repeated Errors**: Same errors appearing across multiple attempts\n2. **Error Evolution**: How errors have changed (or not) between iterations\n3. **Failed Approaches**: What solutions have been tried and failed\n4. **Root Causes**: Underlying issues causing persistent failures\n5. **Unresolvable Patterns**: Errors that indicate fundamental blockers\n\nLook specifically for:\n- Identical error messages in previous task executions\n- Similar failures with the same root cause\n- Attempts that keep failing for the same reason\n- Configuration or permission errors that persist\n- External dependencies that remain unavailable\n\n## Validation Criteria:\n\n1. **Completeness**: Have all required tasks been executed?\n2. **Success**: Did tasks meet their individual success criteria?\n3. **Integration**: Do the results work together cohesively?\n4. **User Needs**: Does the outcome satisfy the original request and objective?\n5. **Quality**: Is the solution robust and well-implemented?\n6. **Error Patterns**: Are we stuck in a loop of repeated failures?\n\n## Decision Points:\n\n### Continue Loop If:\n- Critical tasks failed but the error is NEW or different from previous attempts\n- A different approach might succeed\n- Results are incomplete but progress is being made\n- Quality improvements are achievable\n- Not at max iterations yet AND there's a clear path forward\n\n### Complete Loop If:\n- All success criteria are met\n- User request is fully satisfied\n- Maximum iterations reached\n- No meaningful improvements possible\n- Partial success is the best achievable outcome\n\n### Abort with Unresolvable Errors If:\n- Same errors have appeared in multiple previous attempts (check conversation history)\n- Critical errors that cannot be fixed through iteration\n- External dependencies that are consistently unavailable\n- Configuration issues requiring manual intervention\n- Security or compliance violations blocking execution\n- Fundamental misunderstanding requiring user clarification\n- Clear pattern of repeated failures with no progress\n\n## Important:\n- **ALWAYS** check conversation history for previous error occurrences\n- Be honest about repeated failures and stuck patterns\n- Consider partial success scenarios\n- Provide clear reasoning based on pattern analysis\n- If continuing, explain why this attempt will be different\n- If completing, focus on whether the objectives were met\n- If aborting, clearly explain the repeated pattern and what cannot be resolved"
        }
      ]
   },
  "contents": [
    {{#each conversation_history}}
    {
      "role": "{{this.role}}",
      "parts": [
        {
          "text": "{{this.content}}"
        }
      ]
    }{{#unless @last}},{{/unless}}
    {{/each}}
  ],
  "generationConfig": {
    "responseMimeType": "application/json",
    "responseSchema": {
      "type": "OBJECT",
      "properties": {
        "validation_result": {
          "type": "OBJECT",
          "properties": {
            "overall_success": {
              "type": "BOOLEAN",
              "description": "Whether the execution met success criteria"
            },
            "completeness_score": {
              "type": "NUMBER",
              "description": "Percentage of completion (0-100)"
            },
            "quality_assessment": {
              "type": "STRING",
              "enum": ["excellent", "good", "acceptable", "needs_improvement", "poor"],
              "description": "Quality of the solution"
            },
            "issues_found": {
              "type": "ARRAY",
              "items": {
                "type": "STRING"
              },
              "description": "List of issues or gaps identified"
            },
            "achievements": {
              "type": "ARRAY",
              "items": {
                "type": "STRING"
              },
              "description": "What was successfully accomplished"
            }
          },
          "required": ["overall_success", "completeness_score", "quality_assessment", "issues_found", "achievements"]
        },
        "loop_decision": {
          "type": "STRING",
          "enum": ["continue", "complete", "abortunresolvable"],
          "description": "Whether to continue the loop, complete, or abort due to unresolvable errors"
        },
        "decision_reasoning": {
          "type": "STRING",
          "description": "Detailed explanation for the loop decision, including analysis of error patterns from conversation history"
        },
        "next_iteration_focus": {
          "type": "STRING",
          "description": "If continuing, what to focus on next and why it will be different",
          "nullable": true
        },
        "has_unresolvable_errors": {
          "type": "BOOLEAN",
          "description": "Whether there are errors that cannot be resolved through iteration (based on pattern analysis)"
        },
        "unresolvable_error_details": {
          "type": "STRING",
          "description": "If has_unresolvable_errors is true, detailed explanation including the repeated pattern observed",
          "nullable": true
        },
        "detected_error_patterns": {
          "type": "ARRAY",
          "description": "List of error patterns detected from conversation history",
          "items": {
            "type": "OBJECT",
            "properties": {
              "error_type": {
                "type": "STRING",
                "description": "Type or category of the error"
              },
              "occurrences": {
                "type": "NUMBER",
                "description": "How many times this error appeared"
              },
              "first_seen": {
                "type": "STRING",
                "description": "When this error was first encountered"
              },
              "is_recurring": {
                "type": "BOOLEAN",
                "description": "Whether this error keeps appearing"
              }
            },
            "required": ["error_type", "occurrences", "is_recurring"]
          }
        }
      },
      "required": ["validation_result", "loop_decision", "decision_reasoning", "has_unresolvable_errors", "detected_error_patterns"]
    },
    "temperature": 0.6,
    "maxOutputTokens": 4096,
    "thinkingConfig": {
      "thinkingBudget": 256
    }
  }
}